========================================================================================
DOM ACCESSING:
val():
val function is used to set or get value of from control.

Syntax of Value:
var variable_name=$("selector").val();

Example:
<input type="text" id="txt"/>
var txtv=$("#txt").val();

Syntax of Set VAlue of Form Control:
$("selector").val(value);

Example:
<input type="text" id="txt1"/>
<input type="text" id="txt2"/>
var v=$("#txt1").val();
$("#txt2").val(v);

OR
$("#txt2").val("RANJANA");
=======================================================================================
text():
text function is used to set/get normal text of selected html element.

Syntax of get text:
var txtv=#("selector").text();

Example:
var dvtxt=("#dv").text();
----
Syntax of set text:
#("selector").text(value);

Example:
<div id="dv">HELLO </div>
<h1 id="h"></h1>
var dvtxt=("#dv").text();
$("#h").text(dvtxt);
OR
$("#h").text("CONGRATULATIONS !");

======================================================================================
html:
======================================================================================
css():
css function is used to set single or multiple css at a time based on css property and value.

Single Css:
-----------
$("selector").css("propertyName","value");

Example:
<div id="dv"></div>
$("#dv").css("height","200px");
$("#dv").css("width","200px");
$("#dv").css("background-color","lime");

================
Multiple Css:
-----------
$("selector").css({propertyName1:"value1",propertyName2:"value2",.....,propertyNameN:"valueN"});


Example:
<div id="dv"></div>
$("#dv").css({height:"200px",width:"200px",backgroundColor:"lime",boxShadow:"0px 0px 2px red"});

==============================================================================================
attr():
-------
attr function is used to get/set attribute of selected html element.

Syntax:
Get:
var variable_name=$("selector").attr("attribute_name");

Example:
<img src="path.png" id="img1"/>
var path=$("#img1").attr("src");

Set:
Syntax:
$("selector").attr("attribute_name","value");

Example:
<input type="checkbox"/>
$("input").attr("type","text");
=============================================================================================
prop():
prop function is used to get or set property of selected html element.

Syntax:
Get:
----
var variable_name=$("selector").prop();

Set:
----
$("selector").prop("propertyName","value");

=============================================================================================
addClass():
addClass function is used to add css class to the selected html element.

Syntax:
$("selector").addClass("className");

Example:
<style>
.im{
height:300px;

}
</style>
$("img").addClass(".im");
or
$("img").addClass('.im');
=============================================================================================
removeClass():
removeClass function is used to remove applied class from selectd html element.

Syntax:

$("selector").removeClass("className");


============================================================================================
toggleClass():
toggleClass function is used to provide toggle between addClass and removeClass.

Syntax:
$("selector").toggleClass("className");

============================================================================================
hasClass():
hasClass function is used to check defined class is added or not.
its returns true if given class is added on selected html element otherwise returns false.


Syntax:
var variable_name=$("selector").hasClass("className");

============================================================================================
hide():
hide function is used to hide a selected html element basis on the speed.

Syntax:
$("selector").hide(speed);

speed value:
1)"fast"
2)"slow"
3)"medium"
4)Time in miliseconds like(2000)

Example:
--------
$("div").hide("fast");
$("div").hide(2000)
============================================================================================
show():
show function is used show to show a selected html element based on tne speed.

Syntax:
$("selector").show(speed);

Example:
--------
$("div")

============================================================================================
toggle():
toggle function is used to toggle between hide and show function.


Syntax:
$("selector").toggle(speed);


============================================================================================
slideUp():

Example:
<html>
<head>
<style>
img{
height:200px;
width:220px;
border:2px solid lime;
padding:10px;
margin:20px;
}
</style>
<script src="js/jquery.min.js"></script>
<script>
$(document).ready(function(){
$("#btn1").click(function(){
$("img").slideUp(2000);
})

$("#btn2").click(function(){
$("img").slideDown(2000);
})

$("#btn3").click(function(){
$("img").slideToggle(2000);
})
})
</script>
</head>
<body>
<center>
<img src="images/p1.jpg"/>
<img src="images/p3.jpg"/>
<img src="images/p4.jpg"/>
<img src="images/p5.jpg"/><br/><br/><br/><br/><br/>
<button id="btn1">slideUp</button>
<button id="btn2">slideDown</button>
<button id="btn3">slideToggle</button>
</center>
</body>
</html>
