=========================
fadeIn():
fadeOut():
fadeToggle():
fadeTo():

Example:
<html>
<head>
<style>
#box{
height:300px;
width:400px;
background:lime;
border:5px double purple;
padding:20px;
margin:20px 40px;
float:left;
}
img{
height:300px;
width:400px;
border:10px double maroon;
padding:20px;
float:right;
}
</style>
<script src="js/jquery.min.js"></script>
<script>
$(document).ready(function(){
$("#btn1").click(function(){
$("#box").fadeIn("fast");
$("img").fadeIn("slow");
})

$("#btn2").click(function(){
$("#box").fadeOut(2000);
$("img").fadeOut(3000);
})

$("#btn3").click(function(){
$("#box").fadeToggle(3000);
$("img").fadeToggle(4000);
})

$("#btn4").click(function(){
$("#box").fadeTo(2000,.3);
$("img").fadeTo(3000,.2);
})
})
</script>
</head>
<body>
<div id="box"></div>
<img src="images/p5.jpg">
<br/><br/><br/>
<button id="btn1">fadeIn</button>
<button id="btn2">fadeOut</button>
<button id="btn3">fadeToggle</button>
<button id="btn4">fadeTo</button>
</body>
</html>
========================
animation():
animation function is used to create custom animation based on css property and value.

Syntax:
$("selector").animate({propertyName1:"value1",propertyName2:"value2",.......,propertyNameN:"valueN"},speed)

Example:
<html>
<head>
<style>
#box{
height:100px;
width:100px;
background:maroon;
position:absolute;
}
</style>
<script src="js/jquery.min.js"></script>
<script>
$(document).ready(function(){
$("button").click(function(){
$("#box").animate({border:"20px double hotpink",opacity:".4",right:"0px"},2000);
$("#box").animate({bottom:"0px"},2000);
$("#box").animate({left:"0px"},2000);
$("#box").animate({top:"0px"},2000);
})
})
</script>
</head>
<body>
<button>ANIMATE</button>
<div id="box"></div>
</body>
</html>
===================================================================================================================
append():
prepend():
after():
before():

1)append():
append function is used to add content at the end of selected HTML element.

Syntax:
$("selector").append("Content_which_u_want_to_add");

Example:
$("div").append("<img src='images/p1.jpg'/>");

===================================================================================================================
prepend():
prepend function is use to add content starting of the selected html element.

Syntax:
$("selector").prepend("Content_which_u_want_to_add");

Example:
$("div").prepend("<img src='images/p1.jpg'/>");
==================================================================================================================

after():
after function is used to add content after selected html element.

Syntax:
$("selector").after("content");

======================
before():
before function is used to add content before selected html element.

Syntax:
$("selector").before("content");

